Windows.ApplicationModel.Background.Devi: Represents an event that causes a background task to run when changes occur to the list of devices. Returned by GetBackgroundTrigger.
Windows.Data.Json.JsonObject: Represents a JSON object containing a collection of name and [JsonValue] pairs.
Windows.Data.Json.JsonValue: Implements the [IJsonValue] interface which represents a JSON value.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.IXmlNode: Contains information for the entire Document Object Model. This interface represents a single node in the document tree. While all objects that implement this interface expose methods for dealing with children, not all objects that implement this interface may have children.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlAttribute: Represents an attribute of an XmlElement. Valid and default values for the attribute are defined in a document type definition (DTD) or schema.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlCDataSection: Represents a CDATA section of an XML document.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlDocument: Represents the top level of the XML source. This class includes members for retrieving and creating all other XML objects.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlDocumentFragment: Represents a lightweight object that is useful for tree insertion operations.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlDocumentType: Contains information associated with the document type.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlDomImplementatio: Provides methods that are independent of any particular instance of the document object model.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlElement: Encapsulates information specific to XML Element nodes.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlLoadSettings: Contains settings that are used during loading and parsing of XML documents. The default settings are chosen for the highest security. This class can be instantiated and is accepted by LoadXml, LoadFromUriAsync, and LoadFromFileAsync.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlNamedNodeMap: Encapsulates iteration through the collection of attribute nodes.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlProcessingInstru: Represents a processing instruction, which XML defines to keep processor-specific information in the text of the document.
Windows.Data.Xml.Dom.XmlText: Represents the text content of an element.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.DeviceInform: Represents a device. This class allows access to well-known device properties as well as additional properties specified during device enumeration.
Represents a collection of DeviceInformation objects.
Represents a custom pairing for a DeviceInformation object.
Contains information and enables pairing for a device.
Contains updated properties for a DeviceInformation object.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.DevicePairin: Contains information about the result of attempting to pair a device.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.DevicePicker: Represents a picker flyout that contains a list of devices for the user to choose from.
Represents the appearance of a device picker.
Represents the filter used to determine which devices to show in the device picker. The filter parameters are OR-ed together to build the resulting filter.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.DeviceThumbn: Represents the thumbnail image for a device.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.DeviceUnpair: Contains information about the result of attempting to unpair a device.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.DeviceWatche: Enumerates devices dynamically, so that the app receives notifications if devices are added, removed, or changed after the initial enumeration is complete.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.EnclosureLoc: Describes the physical location of a device in its enclosure.
Windows.Devices.Enumeration.IDevicePairi: Identifies a collection of settings for device pairing. WiFiDirectConnectionParameters implements IDevicePairingSettings.
Windows.Devices.Geolocation.Geocoordinat: Contains the information for identifying a geographic location.
Provides additional information about a Geocoordinate. This information is only applicable to position estimates obtained using satellite signals.
Windows.Devices.Geolocation.Geolocator: Provides access to the current geographic location.
Windows.Devices.Geolocation.Geoposition: Represents a location that may contain latitude and longitude data or venue data.
Windows.Devices.Geolocation.VenueData: Represents the venue associated with a geographic location.
Windows.Devices.Power.BatteryReport: Provides properties that indicate the charge, capacity, and status of the battery.
Windows.Devices.Sensors.PedometerReading: Provides an interface for a pedometer to measure the number of steps taken.
Windows.Foundation.Collections.IProperty: Represents a collection of key-value pairs, correlating several other collection interfaces.
Windows.Foundation.Collections.PropertyS: Represents a property set, which is a set of [PropertyValue] objects with string keys.
Windows.Foundation.Collections.StringMap: An associative collection, also known as a map or a dictionary.
Windows.Foundation.Collections.ValueSet: Implements a map with keys of type String and values of type Object. Object must be a WinRT [PropertyValue] or [ValueSet]. As a [PropertyValue], it can be any type except [PropertyType] `InspectableArray`. This limitation exists to ensure that the value can be serialized; passed by value across a process boundary.
Windows.Foundation.IAsyncAction: Represents an asynchronous action. This is the return type for many Windows Runtime asynchronous methods that don't have a result object, and don't report ongoing progress.
Windows.Foundation.IAsyncInfo: Supports asynchronous actions and operations. `IAsyncInfo` is a base interface for `IAsyncAction`, `IAsyncActionWithProgress<TProgress>`, `IAsyncOperation<TResult>` and `IAsyncOperationWithProgress<TResult,TProgress>`, each of which support combinations of return type and progress for an asynchronous method.
Windows.Foundation.IClosable: Defines a method to release allocated resources.
Windows.Foundation.IPropertyValue: Represents a value in a property store.
Windows.Foundation.IStringable: Provides a way to represent the current object as a string.
Windows.Foundation.PropertyValue: Represents a value in a property store (such as a [PropertySet] instance).
Windows.Foundation.Uri: Defines an object that represents a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) value and parses it into components. The Uri object is used by many other Windows Runtime APIs that are not necessarily confined to web browser scenarios.
Windows.Foundation.WwwFormUrlDecoder: Parses a URL query string, and exposes the results as a read-only vector (list) of name-value pairs from the query string.
Windows.Foundation.WwwFormUrlDecoderEntr: Represents a name-value pair in a URL query string.
Windows.Gaming.Input.Headset: Contains information about an audio headset attached to a gamepad.
Windows.Globalization.Calendar: Manipulates the representation of a `DateTime` within a given calendar and clock.
Windows.Globalization.Collation.Characte: A container for character group information. Characters are grouped in an index that enables an application to determine where the grouping boundaries are.
Contains the set of character groups and the functionality to get the label for any given string.
Windows.Globalization.NumberFormatting.I: An interface that returns rounded results for provided numbers of several data types.
Rounds numbers to a specified increment.
Windows.Globalization.NumberFormatting.N: Translates digits of the Latin numerical system into digits of another numerical system.
Windows.Globalization.NumberFormatting.S: Rounds numbers to a specified number of significant digits.
Windows.Graphics.Printing3D.Printing3DMu: Represents a combination of properties and/or materials from the material groups specified in `MaterialGroupIndices`.
Windows.Media.MediaProperties.MediaPrope: Represents a set of media properties.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.Attribut: Provides access to property values containing information on current usage of the attributed network connection.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.Connecti: Provides access to property values that indicate the current cost of a network connection.
Represents a network connection, which includes either the currently connected network or prior network connections. Provides information about the connection status and connectivity statistics.
The ConnectionProfileFilter class defines a set of properties that are used to improve the relevance of FindConnectionProfilesAsync results.
Provides the start time and duration for an established or prior connection.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.DataPlan: Represents the current status information for the data plan associated with a connection.
Represents data plan specific data usage information for a connection.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.DataUsag: Represents data usage information returned by the ConnectionProfile.GetLocalUsage method.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.IPInform: Represents the association between an IP address and an adapter on the network.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.LanIdent: Represents physical identification data for a specific NetworkAdapter object. For a code example showing how to retrieve data represented by a LanIdentifier object, see How to retrieve network adapter and locality information (XAML).
Represents the port specific data that enables LAN locality capabilities.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.NetworkI: Provides access to network connection information for the local machine.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.NetworkS: Represents the current network security settings.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.NetworkU: Represents network usage statistics returned by the ConnectionProfile.GetNetworkUsageAsync method.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.Provider: Represents provider network usage statistics returned by the ConnectionProfile.GetProviderNetworkUsageAsync method.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.ProxyCon: Represents the proxy configuration for the current user.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.WlanConn: Used to access information specific to a WLAN connection.
Windows.Networking.Connectivity.WwanConn: Used to access information specific to a WWAN connection.
Windows.Networking.EndpointPair: Provides data for the local endpoint and remote endpoint for a network connection used by network apps.
Windows.Networking.HostName: Provides data for a hostname or an IP address.
Windows.Networking.NetworkOperators.Netw: Provides the ability to configure and create an object that contains a specific tethering network SSID, and specifies the passphrase used to authenticate clients trying to establish a network connection to the tethering network.
Contains details about a tethering client.
This interface exposes the methods and properties used to control and configure tethering capabilities for a specific network account.

Represents the results of a StartTetheringAsync or StopTetheringAsync operation. In addition to the TetheringOperationStatus value, it can include an optional error message string that provides mobile operator specific context to the error.
Windows.Storage.FileProperties.BasicProp: Provides access to the basic properties, like the size of the item or the date the item was last modified, of the item (like a file or folder).
Windows.Storage.FileProperties.DocumentP: Provides access to the document-related properties of an item (like a file or folder).
Windows.Storage.FileProperties.ImageProp: Provides access to the image-related properties of an item (like a file or folder).
Windows.Storage.FileProperties.MusicProp: Provides access to the music-related properties of an item (like a file or folder).
Windows.Storage.FileProperties.StorageIt: Provides access to the content-related properties of an item (like a file or folder).
Represents the thumbnail image associated with a system resource (like a file or folder).
Windows.Storage.FileProperties.VideoProp: Provides access to the video-related properties of an item (like a file or folder).
Windows.Storage.KnownFolders: Provides access to common locations that contain user content. This includes content from a user's local libraries (such as Documents, Pictures, Music, and Videos), HomeGroup, removable devices, and media server devices.
Windows.Storage.Pickers.FileOpenPicker: Represents a UI element that lets the user choose and open files. In a desktop app, before using an instance of this class in a way that displays UI, you'll need to associate the object with its owner's window handle.
Windows.Storage.Pickers.FileSavePicker: Represents a file picker that lets the user choose the file name, extension, and storage location for a file.
Windows.Storage.Pickers.FolderPicker: Represents a UI element that lets the user choose folders.
Windows.Storage.Search.QueryOptions: Specifies the parameters of a search query for enumerating the contents of storage folders.
Windows.Storage.Search.StorageFileQueryR: Provides access to the results of a query of the files in the location that is represented by a StorageFolder object. You can use StorageFileQueryResult to enumerate the files in that StorageFolder location.
Windows.Storage.Search.StorageFolderQuer: Provides access to the results of a query that lists the folder (or file groups) in the folder being queried (which is represented by a StorageFolder). You can use a StorageFolderQueryResult to enumerate folders or file groups in that folder.
Windows.Storage.Search.StorageItemQueryR: Provides access to the results of a query that lists all items including files and folders (or file groups) in the folder being queried (which is represented by a StorageFolder). You can use storageItemQueryResult to enumerate the files and folders in that StorageFolder.
Windows.Storage.StorageFile: Represents a file. Provides information about the file and its content, and ways to manipulate them.
Windows.Storage.StorageFolder: Manages folders and their contents and provides information about them.
Windows.Storage.StorageLibraryChange: Represents a change to an item in a storage library such as the documents, music, or video library.
Windows.Storage.StorageLibraryChangeRead: Enables the calling app to read through the changes to items in a storage library.
Windows.Storage.StorageLibraryChangeTrac: Provides APIs that you can use to manage change tracking for any library (such as documents, music, or videos) or folder.
Allows callers to call EnableWithOptions on the change tracker to choose to track all changes including last change id, or just the last change id.
Windows.Storage.StorageProvider: Contains info about the service that stores files and folders. Files and folders may be stored either by the local file system or by a remote service like Microsoft OneDrive.
Windows.Storage.StorageStreamTransaction: Represents a write transaction for a random-access stream.
Windows.Storage.Streams.IBuffer: Represents a referenced array of bytes used by byte stream read and write interfaces. Buffer is the class implementation of this interface.
Windows.Storage.Streams.IRandomAccessStr: Supports random access of data in input and output streams.
Supports random access of data in input and output streams for a specified data format.
Windows.Storage.UserDataPaths: Returns full paths for common user data folders. User data folders are based on the KNOWNFOLDERID naming pattern.
Windows.System.Power.PowerManager: Provides access to information about a device's battery and power supply status.
Windows.System.UserWatcher: Provides events that fire during enumeration of users, when the collection of users changes, or when a user's authentication status changes.
Windows.UI.Notifications.NotificationDat: Stores data for display in a toast notification.
Windows.UI.Notifications.ScheduledToastN: Contains the XML that defines the toast notification that will display at the scheduled time.
Windows.UI.Notifications.ToastCollection: Represents a group of notifications for a particular app.
Provides methods for creating, retrieving, updating, and removing ToastCollection objects.
Windows.UI.Notifications.ToastNotificati: Defines the content, associated metadata and events, and expiration time of a toast notification.
Manages the toast notifications for an app including the ability the clear all toast history and removing individual toasts.

Creates ToastNotifier objects that you use to raise toast notifications. This class also provides access to the XML content of the system-provided toast templates so that you can customize that content for use in your notifications.

Creates ToastNotifier objects that you use to raise toast notifications for the bound user. This class also provides access to the XML content of the system-provided toast templates so that you can customize that content for use in your notifications.
Windows.UI.Notifications.ToastNotifier: Raises a toast notification to the specific app to which the ToastNotifier is bound. This class also lets you schedule and remove toast notifications.
Windows.UI.ViewManagement.UISettings: Contains a set of common app user interface settings and operations.
